  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for curl",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for curl fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2022-27781: Fixed an issue where curl will get stuck in an infinite\n  loop when trying to retrieve details about a TLS server's certificate chain (bnc#1199223).\n- CVE-2022-27782: Fixed an issue where TLS and SSH connections would\n  be reused even when a related option had been changed (bsc#1199224).\n- CVE-2022-32206: Fixed an uncontrolled memory consumption issue caused\n  by an unbounded number of compression layers (bsc#1200735).\n- CVE-2022-32208: Fixed an incorrect message verification issue when\n  performing FTP transfers using krb5 (bsc#1200737).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
